<div> </div>
<!--start left column-->
<div class="g12">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p class="p1"><strong>Explore one of Europe’s classic walking areas on this special exclusive tour, with a small group of Inghams guests and an expert mountain guide. Learn about the history of the area, the flora and fauna, and discover the best trails and secrets of this beautiful region. The Wilder Kaiser mountain range is one of the most spectacular massifs in the Alps, and part of Austria’s famous long distance Eagle’s Trail route from East to West. With its rugged cliffs and verdant valleys it is teaming with Alpine flowers and birds, and has been a conservation area since for almost 100 years. Our days include plenty of time for photo and wildlife spotting opportunities, and regular refreshment stops at the rustic mountain alms dotted all around the valley to soak up those panoramic views. From our bases in either Söll or Ellmau, we are able to follow some classic overnight hiking routes, reaching the most magnificent and unspoilt areas in the region, but with the benefit of returning each night to the comfort of your chosen hotel.</strong></p>
</div>
<div> </div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Itinerary</h2>
<p><strong>DAY 1 (MONDAY)</strong><br />9am - 3pm<br />Starting at the Wochenbrunneralm (1080m) we will take the Wilder Kaiser walking trail through an enchanting fairy tale forest to the Gruttenhut (1619m). The path allows us to get up close and personal with the spectacular rock face of the Wilder Kaiser Mountains and enjoy some magnificent views. We then continue our journey further to the Ellmau stone circle, a place of natural energy steeped in history and myth.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 2 (TUESDAY)</strong><br />9am - 3pm<br />Today’s tour has all the ingredients of a classic mountain tour. From the Duxeralm, near Kufstein, we cross the Brentenjoch to the Kaindlhut (1293m) taking in stunning views of both the Zahmer Kaiser and the northern side of the Wilder Kaiser mountain range before climbing the Hochegg (1470m), a small peak in the Wilder Kaiser. When we reach the idyllic alpine pastures of the Walleralm, be sure not to miss out on the opportunity to sample a home brewed beer at the Stoeffelhut. The tour ends at the Hintersteinersee (800m), one of the most beautiful natural lakes in the Tyrol.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 3 (WEDNESDAY)<br /></strong>9am - 3pm<br />From the Wochenbrunneralm we walk to the Gaudeamushut (1263m) and continue on to Brennender Palven (1572m), a viewing point with breathtaking views of the Hohe Tauern mountains and down into the valley. Finally we head towards the Obere Regalm (1315m), one of the most beautiful Alpine huts in the region before finishing our day with a walk down into Going.</p>
<p><strong>DAY 4 (THURSDAY)</strong><br />9am - 3pm<br />Today we explore the many hiking trails of Söll’s highest mountain, the Hohe Salve. We are rewarded at the top with panoramic views of 70 peaks over 3000m. Our tour ends here with a typical Tyrolean meal, perhaps a Tiroler Gröstl served in a frying pan, at the top of one of the Tyrol’s most beautiful vantage points.</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What’s included</h2>
<ul>
<li>EXCLUSIVE TO INGHAMS<br />• Small group tour<br />• 4 full day guided walks with expert mountain guide<br />• FREE 6 day walker’s lift pass<br />• FREE Alpine flower guide book<br />• FREE Alpine animals guide book<br />• FREE walking map<br />• FREE daily packed lunch<br />NB. Each day we will stop for lunch or refreshments at a rustic mountain alm. Those who prefer a packed lunch can make a picnic stop nearby. Suitable for keen walkers with a reasonable level of fitness. No mountaineering experience is required. Walks may vary from those shown. <br />Please note that we act at all times as selling agent for the suppliers of activities &amp; excursions.</li>
</ul>
